By Ikenna Uwadileke Abuja  –  The Chief Whip of the Senate, Orji Kalu, on Tuesday in Abuja, lamented the passing of Mallam Wada Maida, Board Chairman of the News Agency of Nigeria (NAN).Kalu in a condolence message said that Maida would be remembered for his objectivity in the course of his professional career.The former governor of Abia commiserated with the government and people of Katsina State, NAN, the Nigerian Guild of Editors and other professional bodies on the loss.While acknowledging the robust contributions of the deceased to the media profession across the globe, Kalu described the death of Maida as a painful loss not only to the media industry but Nigeria at large.According to Kalu, the good deeds of the deceased will continue to speak for him.“The death of Mallam Wada Maida, Board Chairman the News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) is a huge loss to the country.“The deceased contributed to nation building through his professional career and was gentle, calm, objective and forthright in his endeavours.“The late Maida lived a fulfilled life and left behind worthy legacies,” Kalu said.He prayed to Allah to grant the deceased Al-Jannah Firdaus and urged the Maida family to take solace in the fact that their late patriarch lived a purposeful life. (NAN) By Kevin Okunzuwa Benin - Former President, Nigerian Union of Journalists(NUJ), Chief George Izobo, has commiserated with the family of late Malam Wada Maida, ex-Managing Director of the News Agency of Nigeria (NAN). Izobo, who also retired from NAN as an Editor, described Maida’s death as shocking, in a telephone… August 18, 2020 In "News" President Muhammadu Buhari's former Chief Press Secretary, Wada Maida is dead. He was Buhari's Press Secretary when he ruled Nigeria as military Head of State in 1984. Until his death, Maida was a member of the Executive Board of International Press Institute (IPI) and the Chairman of Board of Directors… August 18, 2020 In "Politics" By Ikenna Uwadileke Abuja - The Chief Whip of th